detaileddescription.para:
pxTask
Handle of the task to be queried. Passing a NULL handle results in the priority of the calling task being returned.
The priority of pxTask. Example usage: void vAFunction( void ) { xTaskHandle xHandle;

para.preformatted:
Use the handle to obtain the priority of the created task.
It was created with tskIDLE_PRIORITY, but may have changed
it itself.
	 if( uxTaskPriorityGet( xHandle ) != tskIDLE_PRIORITY )
	 {
The task has changed it's priority.
	 }

Is our priority higher than the created task?
	 if( uxTaskPriorityGet( xHandle ) < uxTaskPriorityGet( NULL ) )
	 {
Our priority (obtained using NULL handle) is higher.
	 }
 }
